<TITLE> BNP council 'to focus on democracy' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 05 (bdnews24.com)  BNP secretary-general Khandaker Delwar Hossain has criticised the government for failing to ensure peoples' welfare and said his party will give direction to the nation from the Dec 8 national council. "BNP's Dec 08 national council will give direction, which will serve the interest of democracy. Our chairperson will deliver speech regarding the direction," he told reporters on Saturday. Delwar demanded necessary protection from the government for the council as well as BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia. Khaleda Zia, for the third time, was unofficially declared elected unopposed as the chairperson of BNP on Dec 04.
